accessibility.text: How do we solve problems recursively?
How do we solve problems recursively?
When n = 1, Take the only disk from the start tower to the ending tower.
Move n-1 disks from the start to the middle (this problem is 1 disk easier than the starting problem.)
Move 1 disk from the start to the end (the easiest problem).
Move the remaining n-1 disks from the middle to the end.
